"Im not interested in recreating the life, im interested in the fashion"  ğŸ‘ ğŸ‘ ğŸ‘ ğŸ‘  round of applause for something most people fail to realize. youre appreciating the aesthetics of that historical period, not all the cons.
If someone doesn't snap her up for a costume designer for the next historical film, they are idiots.

Thank heavens for the viewpoint expressed by this fantastic artist. Her acknowledgment of the uglier aspects of the past is deeply refreshing, and openness about embracing specifically the aesthetic elements, not the culture itself. As someone who make ... See More

I love how sane she is while doing this. It's simply a passion for a hobby she has talent for, but does not pull her from reality. She appreciates and respects the historical aspects of the clothing  and details, but knows that it is simply just that - a recreation. Beautiful dresses.
Irene  Uh she said there's a ball at Versailles where you dress up. I'm adding this to our Irenna bucket list just so you are aware lol

Welcome to my world, i also love to dress like this. But i used to wear historical lolita to feel that I'm in this era. I also love there dresses how they wear and carry them. It takes time to wear them bit its the most beautiful fashion before.

This is exactly the way I want to dress every day. I get to do so on the occasion, but I tend to lean to a more Rococo modern fusion found within Rococopunk. I definitely feel I'm expressing my true self whenever I dress up in that style
Absolute perfection! I am astounded that you can produce all his while working a full time job! Wonderful work and so inspiring.
Elizabeth   Missy  how amazing!  I love how she describes loving the clothing with also recognizing how difficult life was for many during that time.

Beautiful..how did fashion turn so ugly  ğŸ˜¦  I wish we all had the option to purchase and dress in beautiful fabrics and styles, granted it would be hard to go about everyday life In the dresses shown, but where is the beauty and detail in modern fashion? Only on ones Wedding day can you feel like a princess, sad really x Wow How talented this girl is!

Oh my! I think I found my soulmate (jokes) I too am obsessed with historical sewing, have a regular job but sneakily do it and, also agree with her sentiments about not romanticising the past but loving the textiles.
I have 5 bustle era gowns that make me feel like a goddess.  Fashion history is a fascinating glimpse into the past- in ways that get sort of lost in translation I feel.

I've never seen a video about someone so similar to me. I'm currently studying costuming in undergrad and plan on getting my masters in theater costume design. I'm currently studying the era of King Louis XIV, and the ballet costumes of that time. I'm  ... See More
Stunning creations... and I LOVE that Ms Rossi follows her heart... as should we all! Never stop letting your little light shine  <3

I wish there were more people in the world doing what they like and without taking care of what the others could think about them! More people like her, I mean, she is doing what she likes and she is proud of herself because of that and if people stare or talk or even judge does not count  ğŸ‘ğŸ»
Reincarnation in a way? She seems well grounded sooo Not crazy.. Creative and intriguing,, I like! Go Girl!!
I am a Tudor re-enactor from England. I dance authentic Tudor dances and often walk around English/welsh historical places in Tudor costume especially Stratford on Avon. Love your costumes Lauren
She should have a tv program at least a special so we could learn and watch her. Such an artist with incredible talent..

I love this. I have always wanted a gown from the 1870s. Just to wear in my own home. I have seen people that make them online. I tried one on a couple of years ago and was hooked. I love the fabric,  but mostly it was the rustle of the gown, the swish as you moved. The feeling is incredible.
Iv always loved historical court dresses used to dream of walking around in Tudor court dresses! Glad she's able to live her dream maybe when my kids are older I'l get a chance!
Erika Ghazoul  she says that for one day a year you can go to the palace at Versailles dressed in 18th century gowns and now that is my new life goal

I dress in very 50s attire. I don't want to live in the 50s. I admire the movies and fashion of the golden age of hollywood, but it doesnt mean i want to live in that time. Im glad she made that distinction as well.

What she's doing is amazing - is she open for commissions! That Versailles ball is something I've heard of, and something that I would love to go to too  :3   I would LOVE to commission her - I'm into more modernised/Gothic takes on historical clothes already, and while what I currently wear is more anachronistic, I'd like to have something a bit more historically accurate for events that warrant it.

I'm looking for a costumer to help create some simple, sustainable clothing for my naturalistic world of the future. Friend and message me here; also LIKE and see the moviemaking over at Abby Wize Media and message me thru there too.
Iâ€™m gonna start dressing like this and walking around the city myself.  Monica , will you help me find some appropriate gowns on eBay? cc: Harry

Melissa , I could picture  Emily  wearing these gowns while she goes grocery shopping  ğŸ˜‚  but seriously though...
Very inspiring I was always intrigued by Rocco fashion  :)  it would be cool if she did commissions. That Versailles ball sounds wonderful

Really beautiful work. She's a fantastic artist! What I take personally from this interview is that even though you have a day job, you can still do the thing that drives you on your spare time. I am musician and that's what I've done. Ironically as ar ... See More
I have said so many times that if I could, I would only dress in French court style and this woman is clearly living *my* best life lol. Wow wow wow. I need to get sewing.

I personally adore this aesthetic along with lolita and i'm sure she will get really far with her beautiful designs, I would love to try this style of dress one day instead of the cutesy gothic lolita type just to see the differences.
Lauren is amazing and such a sweet and talented person! Her Instagram is awesome! It's always fun to see what her next creation will be!

This lady is really cool! I kinda do the same thing, but I wear clothes like that of a Victorian British farmer, and I do, for the most part, live in that way, but as a scholar, I think it is absolutely crucial that we never forget our global history.  ... See More

I have always been interested in this I do drawings and color I couldnâ€™t probably so like you do but I imagine just once in my life before I die wearing when your downs I have always wanted to put one on I donâ€™t know how much your dresses are if youâ€™re ... See More
Michele Perez  - Iâ€™ve always loved the time period, always loved the fashion. I want one of her gowns and I want to go to Versailles and Carnaval!! Or maybe a wedding dress.

Beautiful video.  Saw in a dream that was so lucid being a courtesan honesta in Italy.   The fun I had balanced the hard life.  It was exceptional dream that I wrote five pages on.   Great discovering youfrom friend on Facebook and your Instagram account.   Love your dedication to textiles and fine detail.
You need to seriously create a piece for Jackie Siegel (of that Queen Of Versailles house down in FL) for when she and her hubby finally have it finished!
I know youâ€™d appreciate this  Kali Schellie . Vintage/historical fashion. I bet she could make some amazing pin up outfits!
They didn't wash much in those days, sometimes they had livestock in their piled up hair! Privileged rich not always so flash.... Wonderful clothing indeed...  â¤ ğŸ’

So beautiful...do you sell these dresses? Their very beautiful, I'd love one but unfortunately I wouldn't be able to afford one, I'm sure their very expensive... For all the work you put in it...still very beautiful
I am a deeply passionate 18th century buff and this is my dream- I would love one of these dresses and I would most definitely wear it around my city without a question of doing
Alix Heugas  remember when we were like "we should bring back 19th century style"? this lady's got the jump on us
Years ago i was sawing Dresses like this for a Theater...they Look like a Dream but feel a bit different  ğŸ˜Š ğŸ˜Š ğŸ˜Š  but all in all,a big beautiful creation  ğŸ‘ ğŸ˜ ğŸ˜Š
What an amazing talent!! Kuddos to her for bd8ng herself and doing what she wants. Love her dresses although the corset i can do without ğŸ˜‚
Beautiful! Loving this and always love the fashion back then. Nowadays it's almost naked or you are not beautiful kinda fashion.
18th Century France was my favorite time period for clothing, furniture, architecture and art. This woman's work is amazing. For me, the wider the paniers the better!
It's absolutely beautiful her grandkids going to see her as a beautiful lady when she was young. And other going to see there grandmothers pic make on Snapchat with a puppy face.
Thank you for recognizing that the period wasn't perfect and doesn't need to be recreated to draw inspiration from the fashion. THANK YOU.
I love the idea of bringing back some of these fashions and incorporating them in a modern way. I love the dresses Keira Knightley wore in Pride and Prejudice.

description: å¼µæ›¼å¨œ Certainly, in the most difficult moments of life you realize who your real friends are and who appreciate you.  Unfortunately, like most friendships, FB friends are going to leave you in the middle of a story. They're gonna post a "like" for the story, but they really don't take time to read your post if they see it's long. More than half of you have stopped or you're gonna stop reading here. Some may have rolled into the next post in their news feed.  Well, I have decided to publish this message in support of very special people for me who lost the battle to this terrible disease and some fortunate to have survived and or continue to fight. These are people I can say they have always lived every day as if it were the most beautiful day! They filled the world with a beautiful smile, and made people around them smile too. In at least two cases they still do every day because I see those smiles often here on FB.  It will be interesting to see who will take the time to read this post; a little test to see who reads, and who shares without reading.  If you've read everything so far, select "like" so I can thank you on your profile.  Cancer is a very invasive and destructive enemy. Even after the end of cancer treatment, the body is devastated and struggle with itself in an attempt to reconstruct and repair the damage caused by radiation, chemotherapy and other agents. It's a very long process.  Don't you think it would be nice to see who can relate to what someone is going through? If you, like me, know someone who is fighting cancer, or if you know someone in remission, or meet someone who lost the battle, please honor by copying and pasting this post on FB.  I think some of my friends are going to post this again, to show their support to their family / friend who may be fighting.  Copy and paste - do not share - this post.  I'd like to know who took a minute of your day to read this and took a second minute to think and honor that "someone".  I did. I hope you do too.  When you've completed this, write "done" in the comments. Thanks
